result.execSummary:
The defendant Julian D Carter was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Julian D Carter is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Julian D Carter was found guilty of Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Court sentences defendant to serve 4 days  in the House of Correction with credit for 4 days, a TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.  Defendant to pay all costs, fees and surcharges by 7-08-2016 or civil judgment.

Defendant Julian D Carter in court with attorney Joel Alan Mogren.  Sarah McNutt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Amended complaint filed.  Count 1:  Possession of Cocaine, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 961.41(3g)(c), a Misdemeanor.  Count 2 remains the same. 

Defense motion to dismiss Count 1 GRANTED by the Court.  

Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant plead not guilty.
